<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="848" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d848">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12643.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Governor Carranza leaves tomorrow for Saltillo. He will not name
                            representatives to confer with the representatives of Carbajal. He will
                            treat with them personally. He is disposed to try his utmost to arrange
                            for a prompt, amicable transfer of government and for the surrender of
                            the army.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>